The article discusses the endorsement of Judge Sonia Sotomayor's nomination to the United States Supreme Court by eight national law enforcement organizations. These organizations believe that Judge Sotomayor's record on crime, as a prosecutor and federal judge, demonstrates her fairness and toughness in upholding the rule of law. The article also highlights Judge Sotomayor's experience as a prosecutor, district court judge, and appellate judge, where she has shown a commitment to tough sentencing and upholding the law. Legal experts and law enforcement professionals have praised her approach to criminal law, noting that she is not biased towards criminals and often rules in favor of the prosecution.